# Implementation Plan: Account & Accounts Ledger Module

This plan details the implementation of the new Account Ledger module and its integration with Receipts, Disbursements, and Expenses modules to correctly track cash and bank balances.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `create_receipt` and `create_disbursement` RPCs will need to be updated to accept an `account_id` and automatically insert a corresponding record into `account_transactions`. We will also need to update the Expense creation logic to deduct from the cash account. 
> 
> Please review the database updates section. Let me know if you prefer to run these DB scripts manually or if I should create Dart migrations for them.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Updates
To track cash/bank balances properly, we will modify the existing functions to log entries into `account_transactions`.
- **Receipts**: Update `create_receipt` RPC. Add parameter `p_account_id INT`. After inserting the receipt and client ledger, insert a `credit` transaction into `account_transactions` with `reference_type = 'receipt'` and the receipt ID.
- **Disbursements**: Update `create_disbursement` RPC. Add parameter `p_account_id INT`. Insert a `debit` transaction into `account_transactions` with `reference_type = 'disbursement'`.
- **Expenses**: We will write a new function or update the dart code to insert a `debit` transaction into `account_transactions` for the default 'cash' account when an expense is added. We might need a configuration or a designated default cash account ID.

### 2. Account Ledger Module (`lib/features/account_ledger`)

#### Domain & Entities
- **[MODIFY]** `domain/entities/account_entity.dart`: Ensure Freezed setup is complete. Add balance computation logic if needed.
- **[NEW]** `domain/entities/account_transaction_entity.dart`: Create Freezed model for `account_transactions` table representing the ledger entries (Date, Credit, Debit, Remarks, etc.).
- **[NEW]** `domain/repositories/account_ledger_repository.dart`: Interface for fetching accounts and their transactions.

#### Data Layer
- **[NEW]** `data/datasource/account_ledger_remote_datasource.dart`: Supabase queries to fetch accounts, their balances, and transaction history. Includes queries to compute the running balance dynamically or use the `balance` field.
- **[NEW]** `data/repositories/account_ledger_repository_impl.dart`: Implementation of the repository.

#### Presentation Layer
- **[NEW]** `presentation/provider/account_ledger_providers.dart`: Riverpod providers for `getAllAccounts`, `getAccountTransactions(accountId)`, etc.
- **[NEW]** `presentation/pages/account_dashboard.dart`: A data table view showing `Account Title | Bank Name | Current Balance`.
- **[NEW]** `presentation/pages/account_details_page.dart`: Drill-down view showing a specific account's transaction history with columns `Date | Credit | Debit | Balance | Remarks`. We will calculate the running balance row by row.

---

